I noticed default keybindings ( on the reference card ) for focus left/up/down/right are vi(m)-keys shifted by one key right, why? Can they be changed?</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Oct 2012 06:09:58 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/641/default-keybinding/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Michael for &lt;p&gt;I currently use dwm with keybindings configured to be very vi(m) like, but I thought I might give i3 a try. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I noticed default keybindings ( on the reference card ) for focus left/up/down/right are vi(m)-keys shifted by one key right, why? Can they be changed?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/641/default-keybinding/?answer=642#post-id-642</link><description>Seriously, your question is "can the key bindings be changed"? :-)

This is a tiling window manager with a declared target audience of power users an developers. **Of course** the keybindings can be changed, see http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#keybindings (which you should have read before asking in the FAQ).

The jkl; question was already asked on the mailing list: http://www.mail-archive.com/i3-discuss@i3.zekjur.net/msg00458.html — in summary: We use jkl; because that’s on your homerow and therefore where your fingers rest when touch-typing anyway.</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Oct 2012 07:10:13 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/641/default-keybinding/?answer=642#post-id-642</guid></item><item><title>Comment by andrnils for &lt;p&gt;Seriously, your question is "can the key bindings be changed"? :-)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a tiling window manager with a declared target audience of power users an developers. &lt;strong&gt;Of course&lt;/strong&gt;the keybindings can be changed, see &lt;a href="http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#keybindings"&gt;http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#k...&lt;/a&gt; (which you should have read before asking in the FAQ).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The jkl; question was already asked on the mailing list: &lt;a href="http://www.mail-archive.com/i3-discuss@i3.zekjur.net/msg00458.html"&gt;http://www.mail-archive.com/i3-discus...&lt;/a&gt; — in summary: We use jkl; because that’s on your homerow and therefore where your fingers rest when touch-typing anyway.&lt;/p&gt;
